msgid ""
"You can skip the hash check by setting the env var "
"`DANGER_PLUGIN_SKIP_HASH_CHECK`."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributors/08-plugins.md:20
msgid ""
"Plugins are implemented using [Extism](https://extism.org/) and Webassembly. "
"They can be written in any language that compiles to Wasm. Checkout the "
"[documentation](https://extism.org/docs/quickstart/plugin-quickstart) for "
"general development instructions."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributors/08-plugins.md:22
msgid ""
"The [lemmy-plugins](https://github.com/LemmyNet/lemmy-plugins/) repo "
"contains various example plugins written in different languages."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributors/08-plugins.md:24
msgid "API `before` hooks"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributors/08-plugins.md:26
msgid ""
"These are called before a given API endpoint is invoked, with the raw JSON "
"data submitted by the user, and need to return data in the same format. "
"Useful for moderation bots which can alter or reject posts."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributors/08-plugins.md:28 src/contributors/08-plugins.md:39
msgid "Examples:"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributors/08-plugins.md:30
msgid ""
"`local_post_before_create` with data [CreatePost](https://github.com/"
"LemmyNet/lemmy/blob/main/crates/db_views/post/src/api.rs#L16)"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributors/08-plugins.md:31
msgid ""
"`local_comment_before_update` with data [EditComment](https://github.com/"
"LemmyNet/lemmy/blob/main/crates/db_views/comment/src/api.rs#L145)"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributors/08-plugins.md:32
msgid ""
"`federated_post_before_receive` with [PostInsertForm](https://github.com/"
"LemmyNet/lemmy/blob/main/crates/db_schema/src/source/post.rs#L97)"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributors/08-plugins.md:33 src/contributors/08-plugins.md:44
msgid "Search the code for `plugin_hook_before` to find all available hooks"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributors/08-plugins.md:35
msgid "API `after` hooks"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributors/08-plugins.md:37
msgid ""
"Called after an endpoint was successfully invoked and gets passed the API "
"return data. Useful for notifications."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributors/08-plugins.md:41
msgid ""
"`local_post_after_create` with data [CreatePost](https://github.com/LemmyNet/"
"lemmy/blob/main/crates/db_views/post/src/api.rs#L16)"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributors/08-plugins.md:42
msgid ""
"`local_comment_after_update` with data [EditComment](https://github.com/"
"LemmyNet/lemmy/blob/main/crates/db_views/comment/src/api.rs#L145)"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributors/08-plugins.md:43
msgid ""
"`federated_post_after_receive` with [Post](https://github.com/LemmyNet/lemmy/"
"blob/main/crates/db_schema/src/source/post.rs#L25)"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributors/08-plugins.md:46
msgid "Captcha Plugin"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributors/08-plugins.md:48
msgid ""
"`get_captcha` generates a new captcha, returns [CaptchaResponse](https://"
"github.com/LemmyNet/lemmy/blob/main/crates/db_views/site/src/api.rs#L353)"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributors/08-plugins.md:49
msgid ""
"`validate_captcha` takes [CaptchaAnswer](https://github.com/LemmyNet/lemmy/"
"blob/141d12d9ab249b3e425313a9e4f59b2410f4b319/crates/db_views/"
"registration_applications/src/api.rs#L69) and should return error if the "
"answer is wrong"
msgstr ""
